<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-03-16T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-03-16T17:00:00-05:00" n="704" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d704">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003/558: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-03-16T17:00:00-05:00">March 16, 1931—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>103. Your 131, March 14, 11 a.m. In view of Legation’s present statement,
                            you may, in your discretion, withhold issuing consular circular or so
                            phrase the circular that it cannot be interpreted as a criticism of
                            Consul Stevens’ efforts to prepare a report on the Chinese judiciary in
                            Yunnan Province.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
